    "body": "Whats the difference between using the configure widget and just adding the\nsearchParameters to the main instaseiarch({}) var?\n\nOn Fri, Jul 13, 2018 at 12:24 PM, Samuel Vaillant <notifications@github.com>\nwrote:\n\n> You have two possible solution to control the number of the hits. The\n> first solution is to use the widget HitsPerPageSelector\n> <https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets/hitsPerPageSelector.html>it\n> will display a select that lets the user control how many hits are\n> displayed. But in case you don't want to let the user choose you can use\n> the Configure\n> <https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets/configure.html>\n> widget.\n>\n> search.addWidget(  instantsearch.widgets.configure({    hitsPerPage: 8,\n>   })\n> );\n>\n> —\n> You are receiving this because you authored the thread.\n> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub\n> <https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/3034#issuecomment-404883222>,\n> or mute the thread\n> <https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/AAgSq-ISCZ-T5UMTsyM3iIVR4-Tj8MRVks5uGMnOgaJpZM4VPAib>\n> .\n>\n\n\n\n-- \nseth giammanco\nseth@mod-lab.com\nph 718.858.1066\n\nminds on design lab\nwww.mod-lab.com\nSubscribe to our Mailing List\n<https://confirmsubscription.com/h/y/12431274F3870FEA>\n",
